<br>
No, why would they? The parent company (SoE) wants money. Verant wanted to make games. I think we have proven to SoE beyond a shadow of a doubt that we are willing to pay them even if they screw the integrity of the game in the asshole until it bleeds and has HIV. Why do they need Verant or integrity?<br>
<br>
I really dont understand why you think it impossible for the people with values to be ousted by/in favor of the people with greed. It happens in many ways and places every day.<br>
<br>
I do not know what relationship Verant originally had with SoE but my understanding is that Sony was the financial backer and Verant was the programming and development team. If Verant (like a Blizzard or Square) had been an established and independant gaming company maybe they would still run it. The fact is that they needed SoE to foot the bill for this venture and because of that SoE has its hands in the mix. By Velious this was a bona fide smash hit wonderchild cash cow. If SoE can keep all the players hooked for many years to come, then sole ownership would be more profitable in the long run. Buying out Verants share of the pie allowed them to cut whatever corners they wanted to and has lead us to this current disgrace of character transfers which Brad and Co. never would have allowed. <br>
<br>
I cannot blame Verant for taking what they could get in the face of pressure to change business practice at the expense of the game. Maybe Sigil can finance thier own venture with whatever was left for them from Everquest and be able to focus on making a gamers game again without being under the yoke of a money sucking multinational corporation.<br>
<br>
I do not work in the industry and I do not know first hand the details of SoE and Verant's partnership or the details of the split, but this much is what I have inferred. If anyone can supply some hard data I would be very interested in seeing it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554649">Fammaden Flycaster</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target="top">Heaven and Earth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suchossuave>Suchos Suave</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.scithe.com/humor/pug.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/21/03 9:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3685.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buy your EQ II beta pass today!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They are not forcing anything upon us, we have a choice to buy or not to buy. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
